verbose_text: Both the canola and the sunflower oil diets increased alpha-tocopherol levels compared to the high-SFA baseline diet, which underscored that these oils are potentially beneficial for reducing the risk of ischemic heart disease in people with low plasma concentrations of vitamin E. XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR Concentrations of gamma-tocopherol decreased after the sunflower oil based diet but did not change following the canola oil based diet.
